<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-2050] Avoid calling .size() on java.util.ConcurrentLinkedQueue</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2050</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Generally, it seems to be preferred to avoid calling .size() on a Java ConcurrentLinkedQueue. This is an O(N) operation as it must iterate through all the nodes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Calling this every time through the loop makes this issue worse under high load. It seems like the same functionality can be attained by just polling and checking for null.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is more imperative and less functional, but it seems alright since this is in lower-level networking code.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
